text: Gasteroclupea is an extinct genus of ellimmichthyiform fish from the Upper Cretaceous of South America. It contains one species, G. branisai. Its closest relative is probably Sorbinichthys. == Related pages == * Sorbinichthys == References == Category:Extinct fish Category:Ray-finned fish Category:Cretaceous Category:Animals of South America
title: Gasteroclupea
